          <h5 class="mt-2">6. Branded Memes</h5>
          <p>Its really hard rather impossible to avoid memes because everyone loves memes and everyone loves to watch, like, comment and share memes with their friends, family and social circle. There is a meme for everything and everything can be turned into a meme.</p>
          <p>Some memes go viral within minutes. Memes once become viral can have a shorter or longer lifespan and we can even see its extended versions as well. Memes can disappear out within a day or within few hours but some of them are evergreen and continue to be recognized years later on as well.
          <br>Brands are now more open to memes and branded memes has become a hot trend. 
          </p>
          <p>Consider the example of Shopify. This meme worked for Shopify because of its simplicity. The actors and the context may not be relevant in a few months but the visual is so simple and attractive that it conveys the story the brand is trying to tell. That is why branded memes are most of the times successful. Keep in mind that the visual used in the meme should stand out on its own. The best memes communicate plenty without any context.</p>
          <img src="media/pages/blog/Branded-Memes.png" class="img-fluid m-2" alt="Branded Memes">
