          <p>At Simplex Outsourcing, we would like to advise you that the use of quotes in visual marketing has evolved. There is certainly a room for quotes in the marketing strategy now but the real hack is to find one soundbite that must stands out and use that for your visual.</p>

          <h5 class="mt-2">8. Social Screencaps</h5>
          <p>Brands are sharing versions of the same post on multiple social media channels for quite a while now but each platform has its unique voice and appeal. It is not always feasible to create separate content all the time. Brands need to share announcements, news, contests or product launches on all social media channels and they want to share it at the same time. The best way to do this is through social media screencaps. They have been gaining popularity not only amongst individuals but also amongst the brands.</p>
          <p>Have a look at <strong>HubSpot’s</strong> Instagram posts, we will often see these types of images appear there. The posts are screenshots of the tweets overlayed on HubSpot’s signature brand visuals.
          <br>This trend is becoming popular and we can’t help but love and adopt it. There is no way to share the posts directly from Twitter to Instagram at the moment as Twitter is a very text-based medium but Instagram is entirely visual but these marketing tips and tricks that <strong>HubSpot</strong> has shared are relevant to their audience. No matter what platform they are on!
          <br><strong>HubSpot</strong> has taken to screenshotting these tweets and sharing them on its Instagram.
          </p>
          <img src="media/pages/blog/Social-Screencaps.png" class="img-fluid m-2" alt="Social Screencaps">
          <p>We will see the graphic trend of social screencaps taking over in time for 2022.
          <br>Brands aren’t just sharing tweets on Instagram and LinkedIn. Zoom is sharing its Tik-Tok videos on the Instagram.
          </p>
          <img src="media/pages/blog/Social-Screencaps2.png" class="img-fluid m-2" alt="Social Screencaps">
          <p>Instagram’s new video settings allow a variety of sizes and Tik-Tok’s vertical orientation fits perfectly on Instagram and Zoom is even sharing their Tik-Toks on Twitter as well.</p>
          <img src="media/pages/blog/Social-Screencaps3.png" class="img-fluid m-2" alt="Social Screencaps">
          <p>At Simplex Outsourcing we brief our clients that users on social media are not there for sale-oriented content but they are rather there to be entertained and to learn quick tips and tricks. Therefore, the success ingredient is to bring multiple platforms together through social screencaps.</p>
